                "name": "David Tuffley",
                "href": "/profile/David-Tuffley-1"
            },
            "answer_text": "Nihilism is defined as the belief that all values are baseless and that nothing can be known or communicated. Often associated with extreme pessimism and a radical skepticism that condemns existence. A nihilist would believe in nothing, have no loyalties, and no purpose other than, perhaps, an impulse to destroy. Taoism emphasizes being in harmony with the Tao which simply means \"way\", \"path\" - the laws of Nature. ",
